sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K223046
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: SoxR - SoxS Promoter System with downstream GFP production. This was used to characterize the inducible oxidative stress signal when activating the SoxR-SoxS promoter system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Was tested on both a high and low copy plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Suzanne Bartram

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K223040
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SoxR Gene: Produces the SoxR protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part produces the SoxR protein, which in the presence of oxidative stresses, such as paraquat and nitric oxide, binds with high affinity to the SoxS promoter. The SoxR generator, when coupled with the SoxS promoter, can be utilized as an inducible sensor for oxidative stress.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Can be put on both a high, pSB1A3 with AmpR, and low copy plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Suzanne Bartram

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K223041
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pseudomonas aeruginosa SoxR Does Not Conform to the Archetypal Paradigm for SoxR- Dependent Regulation of the Bacterial Oxidative Stress Adaptive Response ~Palma et al. http://iai.asm.org/cgi/reprint/73/5/2958?maxtoshow=&HITS=10&hits=10& RESULTFORMAT =&fulltext=coli&searchid=1&FIRSTINDEX=520&resourcetype=HWFIG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The SoxS promoter is activated by the SoxR protein in the presence of oxidative stress, such as Paraquat or Nitric Oxide. It has a high affinity binding with the SoxR protein. It can be used in conjunction with the SoxR gene as an inducible sensor for oxidative stress.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Suzanne Bartram
